        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 3 at 2:35PM PDT until June 3 at 5:15PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 235 PM PDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms producing heavy
rain across the far south Las Vegas Valley near Henderson and
Southern Highlands.  A rain gage at Sloan reported 0.79 inches of
rain in 30 minutes.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Henderson, Anthem, Southern Highlands, Enterprise, Paradise, Seven
Hills, Sloan, Henderson Executive Airport and Black Mtn.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
